\begin_layout Enumerate
Take 
\begin_inset Formula $a=15$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $b=27$
\end_inset

.
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Enumerate
Using the switching algorithm we can find the 
\begin_inset Formula $\text{GCD}\left(a,b\right)$
\end_inset


\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{align*}
27 & =1\cdot15+12\\
15 & =1\cdot12+3\\
12 & =4\cdot3
\end{align*}

\end_inset

which shows that 
\begin_inset Formula $\text{GCD}\left(a,b\right)=3$
\end_inset

.
 We can solve for 
\begin_inset Formula $x$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $y$
\end_inset

 using the steps in the switch algorithm.
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{align*}
3 & =15-12\\
 & =15-\left(27-15\right)\\
 & =2\cdot15-1\cdot27\\
 & =x\cdot15+y\cdot27,
\end{align*}

\end_inset

with 
\begin_inset Formula $x=2$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $y=-1$
\end_inset

.
