\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Enumerate
Using the switching algorithm we can find the 
\begin_inset Formula $\text{GCD}\left(a,b\right)$
\end_inset


\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{align*}
29 & =1\cdot23+6\\
23 & =3\cdot6+5\\
6 & =1\cdot5+1,
\end{align*}

\end_inset

which shows that 
\begin_inset Formula $\text{GCD}\left(a,b\right)=1$
\end_inset

.
 We can solve for 
\begin_inset Formula $x$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $y$
\end_inset

 using the steps in the switch algorithm.
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{align*}
1 & =6-5\\
 & =6-\left(23-3\cdot6\right)\\
 & =4\cdot6-23\\
