\begin_layout Enumerate
Prove or disprove: If 
\begin_inset Formula $c$
\end_inset

 is a positive common divisor of 
\begin_inset Formula $a$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $b$
\end_inset

, and 
\begin_inset Formula $c=ax+by$
\end_inset

 for some 
\begin_inset Formula $x,y\in\mathbb{Z}$
\end_inset

, then 
