\begin_inset Formula $c\mid a$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $c\mid b$
\end_inset

, then 
\begin_inset Formula $c$
\end_inset

 is a common divisor of 
\begin_inset Formula $a$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $b$
\end_inset

.
